{
  "stem": "23428.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And it-- [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] yeah, that's it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We didn't get food or drink or anything before we got to Vienna.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I think so.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I don't think anybody died in that-- in that transport.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It wasn't long enough.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And when we got to Vienna, we had to get out of the car and we lined up again.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There was one line for Mauthausen and one line for Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So that's when I saw my father once more, last time.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And he went to Mauthausen.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we were then taken to a station in Vienna where the guards proceeded to feed us thin beer.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I think it was out of their own pockets, because they felt-- felt sorry for people who hadn't seen water or anything probably for a day.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So-- and then the other thing that happened, we were taken to Auschwitz not in a cattle car, but in a normal, third-class [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] wagon, railroad wagon, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] with again I think it was two SS people, two guards, sitting at the door side of the compartment.",
      "word_count": 53
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And the thing I remember from that trip is that the guards urged us not to worry, that they said they had been not into Auschwitz, which was, obviously-- which was [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] administered by other-- other troops, not-- not the guards from outside.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But they had gotten to the doors of Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And they told us not to worry about it, because they had seen factories there.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They had seen people working.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Probably nothing was going to happen for it-- to it.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
